data.title: Alumni — Lake Washington Physical Therapy
data.text:
Jason James, SPT

Pacific University (2011)

Jason was our first PT intern at LWPT. He worked with Ben and Matt through the summer of 2011. Jason is an avid bike enthusiast and a great friend of Ben's. His Wife Renee' was a student of Ben's in 2000 at Health South and is also Sara Wobker's childhood best friend from Redwood Falls, Minnesota. Jason and Renee' now both own and work at Boones Landing Physical Therapy in Wilsonville.

Jenna Upper Kokes, SPT

University of Montana (2012)

Jenna worked as Matt and Ben's aide while at Redmond Physical Therapy and later became a doctorate student intern while finishing up at the University of Montana. Jenna and her husband Brett now reside in Winthrop and own Winthrop Physical Therapy and Fitness. She achieved her OCS in the Summer of 2014. Great work Jenna from RPT to UM to LWPT to ownership!

High School: Juanita

College: Forhdam University

PT School: Wingate University

Morgan left JHS with a softball scholarship to Fordham university. She mentored with several of our PTs at our Downtown Kirkland Location and successfully applied to Wingate University in North Carolina for their DPT program. We hope to have Morgan back in the PNW by 2021 :)

Bothell High School

Undergrad: Gonzaga University

Graduate: University of Michigan-Flint

Keagan was mentored by both Jessica and Caitlin. He is now off to his last clinical rotation before sitting for his state boards.

College: Saginaw Valley State University

PT School: University of Michigan

Ruth is a DPT student from the University of Michigan in her final year. He was mentored by both Kelly and Matt at our Houghton clinic. She leaves LWPT on her way to complete her final clinical rotation and then sit for her licensure exam.

High School: Bellevue

College: Northwest University

Braedon grew up in Bellevue, WA, where he attended Bellevue High School. His curiosity about physical therapy began with his love of fitness and training. After having physical therapy done for an ankle injury, he knew he wanted to pursue physical therapy. Braedon recently completed his BS in Exercise science and is heading to Grad School!

Bob Left in 2019 to return back to skilled Nursing facility after a great year with our team. You may see many of the articles he wrote on our website as he was a fantastic writer and enjoyed the science and rehab of baseball.

High School: Inglemoor High School

College: Northwest University

Drew grew up in Kenmore, WA. He is pursuing physical therapy because he is able to help people while also combining his interest for sports and physical activity. Drew graduated with s a B.S. in Exercise Science from Northwest University.

Cassidy Brown,

SPT (Student Physical Therapist)

High School: Louisville Kenuckty

Undergrad: Indiana University

Graduate: Indiana State University

Cassidy Brown is originally from Louisville, Kentucky. She attended Indiana University Southeast in New Albany, Indiana, where she earned her Bachelor’s in the Science of Psychology. She is currently in her third year of the Doctor of Physical Therapy Program at Indiana State University in Terre Haute, Indiana. She hopes to one day specialize in pediatrics. Her hobbies include kayaking and hiking.

High School: Juanita

Undergrad: University of Montana

A big welcome to summer intern Noah Kells!

Noah graduated from Juanita High School in 2016. During his time there he ran track and cross-country and was also a part of the school orchestra. Noah currently is attending the University of Montana and majoring in health and human performance with an emphasis on exercise science and minoring in psychology. He also competed on the track and cross-country team at UM.

High School: Lake Washington

Undergrad: MSU- Billings

We welcome LWHS soccer standout and college soccer player Liam Knox to the clinic for the summer. Liam will be shadowing with Mandie and others as he prepares for a future in Physical Therapy. Go Kangs!

Pacific University SPT

Mark grew up on a small ginseng farm in Oregon surrounded by vineyards and grass seed. He attended Oregon State University and went on to receive his BS in Business Management/ International Business in 2011. After a successful internship with Matt and Victor Mark returns to graduate from Pacific University.

High School: Lake Washington High School

College: Pacific Luthern University

Grad: PIMA College

Cameron was a long time contributor to the success of LWPT. He was part of Ben and Matt’s previous clinic Redmond physical therapy as an intern and shadow. He later became a shadow downtown and then an aide for 3 years while he completed his grad program at Pima University. An outstanding aide and person. He is greatly missed :)

High School: Shoreline High School

College: Oregon State University

Savannah grew up in Shoreline, WA where she attended Shorecrest High School. All throughout high school she was involved in soccer, basketball, and track and field. She has always had a passion for sports, but it wasn’t until college when she herniated a disc that she became interested in physical medicine. Savannah received her B.S in Kinesiology from Oregon State University. Savannah plans on applying to graduate programs to be a Physician Assistant. In her spare time, she enjoys exercising and being outdoors.

High School:Arlington

Undergrad: Western Washington University

PT: Pacific University

Ryann grew up in Arlington, WA and attended her undergraduate education at Western Washington University where she received her Bachelor of Science in Kinesiology—Pre-PT. She is currently finishing her Doctorate of Physical Therapy at Pacific University in Oregon where she is set to graduate in May 2020.

Undergraduate: U of California San Diego

DPT: University of Washington

Katie is from Roseville, California and was fortunate to grow up skiing, hiking, and biking in the Sierra Nevada mountains in the Lake Tahoe area. She completed her undergraduate degree as a Regent’s Scholar at the University of California in San Diego, receiving a B.S in Physiology and Neuroscience while working as a backpacking guide and captaining San Diego’s (very unofficial) Quidditch team. Katie completed her DPT internship with Jessica and Mandie over the Winter of 2020 and graduates from UW in Spring 2020. Great work Katie!!

High School: Redmond High School

College: Oregon State University

Ali grew up in Redmond Washington, where she attended Redmond high school. She played many sports in high school including basketball, soccer, and cross county. Ali attended college at Oregon state university graduating with a degree in digital communication arts and a minor in environmental science. She continued to play basketball on a recreational level as well as coaching different teams and camps. Ali along with coaching basketball at RHS, Pinnacle Hoops, has joined the team at Alaska Airlines to help with digital marketing, social media, and community outreach. Ali was critical in the growing of LWPT from 1 to 3 clinics during her time :)

High School: University Prep

College: Syracuse University

DPT: Rocky Mountain College, UT

Mia grew up in Bellevue and attended University Prep for high school. Mia’s interest in PT developed from a rehab experience she had at LWPT while she was still in high school, which led her to study health and exercise science at Syracuse. Since graduating in 2016, she has spent time working seasonally, spending two summers in Grand Teton National Park in Wyoming, and a winter ski instructing in Vail, Colorado. Mia heads off to PT school in Utah at the college of the Rockies. We cannot wait for her return in 2023!

High School: Lake Washington

College: UW

PA School: Pacific University

Laura came to us via a clinic outside of Vancouver WA. She was an amazing addition and we are all excited to have her meet her goals of attending physician assistant professional program at Pacific University. She will be an amazing fit for any physician office in the future and we all look forward to working with her as a colleague.

High School: Inglemoor

College: Pacific University

PT School: Pacific University

Diana was a crucial team member in the launching of our Kenmore clinic in 2019. She heads off to get her DPT at Pacific University and we look forward to here return as a PT!

High School: International School

College: UW

Kayley leaves the Kirkland clinic to do a socially distanced semester abroad with UW. She is also currently the Pre-PT Club president as she applies to grad school in 2021.

High School: Beaverton

College: Pacific University

DPT Program: TBD

Milana returns to Oregon after being a critical part of our Kenmore team for almost a year. We are excited for her return as a PT in the coming years :)

Jessica left LWPT in 2020 after her second child was born. She has since moved to a clinic closer to home. Jessica was a critical part of our team in Kirkland and held numerous leadership positions including the orthopedic journal club and the student coordinator which led her to help mold the staff into better professionals.

We were very sad to have Caitlin leave our Kirkland team. She was a intricate part of the socialization of our staff. Caitlin excelled with patients and physicians while in Seattle. She has since moved to Utah to continue her appreciation of the mountains and hiking. Caitlin is and will be missed.

Justin was a very important part of our team in both Houghton and Kirkland. He has moved on to UW to follow his passion. Neurological injuries, namely concussions. Justin was a professional through and through and many of his great writing can still be found on our website. We look forward to watching Justin continue to push research for the betterment of patients.

Kelly was an aide at Kirkland for nearly 2 years before returning to Houghton as a PT and helped grow the Houghton clinic from 2 PTs to 7. She is now in Issaquah and working closer to her new home.

Rachel Sannicandro is a third year Physical Therapy student at the University of Puget Sound. She completed her Bachelors degree in Exercise Science at Minnesota State University Moorhead. Her hometown is Elmwood Park, IL, where she grew up playing softball and volleyball. She was a collegiate softball player for 4 years and javelin thrower for 1 season. Rachel leaves LWPT after completing her DPT requirements with Victor Kollar as her CI.

Samie worked at both the Kirkland location initially and then full-time at our Houghton location. She leaves in Summer 2021 to pursue her passion of Neuro PT. She is a great person and will be greatly missed.

High School: Inglemoor

College: Western Washington University

DPT: UW 2024

We are super excited and proud to have Zach head off to UW’s DPT program in the fall of 2022. Zach spent nearly 3 years with us in Kirkland as an aide and helped run all aspects of the business. He is an amazing colleague. LWPT cannot wait for him to complete his doctorate and return to the group. Great work Zach!

Catherine was our very first student PT at our West Seattle Location. She worked under Mark and April. She is now practicing in the Pacific Northwest :)

Corwin head off from our West Seattle clinic to take an amazing job in geriatrics and neurology in California. Corwin has been a great addition in both Kirkland and West Seattle.

High School: Seatac

College: Northwest University

Payton leaves Kenmore to pursue a career in medical sales and equipment. We look forward to continuing to cross paths with him in the OR and medical offices in the region.

As the Front Office Manager at Lake Washington Physical Therapy, Monica Figueroa oversaw the expansion of LWPT Kenmore. Under her watch the office grew by 300%. She now heads off to retirement with her husband and 2 daughters where the family will split time between the east and west coast.

High School: Stadium

Undergraduate: UW Graduate: Western University

Alicia leaves her internship with April Johnson to continue to her career in the Tacoma area. She did an amazing job and will be missed.

High School: Los Angeles County High School for the Arts

University: BMus from City University of London

Sara leaves the Kirkalnd clinic after 3+ years to head to graduate school for family counseling. Sara worked with us previously at Redmond PT in the early 2000s and was a critical part of the team.

Manny leaves our team after 3+ years as she and her husband return to their native North Carolina. Manny was an amazing clinician and person to have on our team. She is already missed.

Josie joined our team after leaving California. She was an amazing clinician getting her OCS and manual certification during her tenure. She and her dog have left us to be closer to home. We wish her the best in her next chapter of her career.

Brittany leaves us to return to Wenatchee where she and her husband grew up. Look for Brittany at our continuing education events and our races. She was an amazing PT to have join our team and made our group better for having been with us.

Morgan had a 12 week affiliation at LWPT Houghton with Clinical Instructor Victor Kollar. Morgan has been associated with LWPT since her high school days at Juanita and fun fact, was also who introduced the Kirkland clinic to Manny.

High School: Oak Harbor

College: Washington State University

Aelizah was instrumental in the great launch of our West Seattle clinic. She now took a different role at Seattle’s Children’s Pediatric PT department as she prepares for her next step into a DPT program.

We are excited to announce that Olivia is starting the PTA program at Lake Washington Technical College in Fall of 2022. She was an amazing addition to our team for 2 years. We are excited to see what comes next.

Dianna heads back to Pacific university after completion of her 16 week internship with Kerri Smith. We hope to have her back in the future. If you would like to watch her in-service on bracing the link is below.

In-service

Nate Leaves redmond after a great application session which saw him get into 4+ schools. He is our 127th Aide to head off to grad school!

Alicia leaves LWPT Kirkland after 2 years as our lead aide and helping the team navigate COVID. She is deeply missed and we hope to have her return to the team after completing her doctorate at UW!

Wes was accepted at UW, Baylor, NC, and choose Duke! Wes was an amazing steady hand in our Kenmore clinic and will make an amazing PT!

Allen was a great team member in our Kenmore location and we are excited to have him stay near by at UW for DPT school.

#133

Josh completed a 14 week rotation with Kirkland therapist Kerri Smith. Josh was outstanding with clients and we look forward to watching his career unfold.

Gus leaves our team in Kenmore after a great 2 years with LWPT! He is moving back to California. Gus was also a student at our Houghton location with Nick Jackson fellow EWU alum. Gus will be greatly missed and is always welcomed back!

After a successful career at WSU and amazing aide work at both Kirkland and West Seattle, Nancy heads off to PT school at Pacific University :) #134

Dominic leaves in July 2023 as he heads off to U of St Augustine in San Diego for his DPT (#135)!

Kathy moved from the Kirkland area to California to have more time with family. She will be missed :)

Stephanie returned to finish up her final prerequisites at Washington State University. Her time in Houghton was fantastic and she will make a great PT in the not so distant future :)

Julia completed her DPT Internship with our student coordinator Katie Hutchins and Woodinville owner Jordan Bork. Julia was our very first OSU Cascades intern in their inaugural cohort!

Kate was an amazing team member at our Kirkland clinic for nearly 2 years while finishing up school at UW. She is off to enjoy, be challenged, and learn the PCT. She will make a huge impact in our community what every career path she chooses :)

Tyler spent nearly 2 years at our Kirkland clinic while at UW and immediately after graduation. Now he heads to one of the top PT programs in the county! He is our 142nd to head off to graduate school.

Kate was with our team in Houghton for nearly 2 years and after much contemplation decided to leave the healthcare space and become a project manager. She was a great person to have part of our team and is missed :)

Averly was a a great fit and amazing aide at our Redmond clinic. She is now in the DPT program at Pacific University!
